# Boating/cannon/set-sails.razor
# Hotkey-bindable: click the enemy ship's sails (or any part) to save it as the
# cannon aim target. Future cannon fires will target this serial automatically.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Bind this script to a key
#   2. When near an enemy ship, press the key
#   3. Click the enemy ship sails / hull / mast
#   4. Debug info overhead tells you what was clicked and its serial
#   5. Re-run whenever you switch targets or the serial goes stale
#
# NOTE: The saved serial is the specific object you clicked (e.g. the Sails tile).
#   If the ship rotates or moves far away, the cannon may still fire at that location.
#   If targeting fails with "cannot reach", re-run this script on the new position.
#   Use Boating\set-target.razor to set an explicit override (ManualTargetEnemy) instead.

clearsysmsg
overhead "Click the enemy ship to aim cannons..." 88
hotkey 'Set Last Target'
wft 3000
while targetexists
    pause 50
endwhile

if not targetexists
    getlabel lasttarget saillabel
    overhead ">>> Clicked: {{saillabel}}" 44
    overhead ">>> Serial stored as ShipSails" 44
    @setvar "ShipSails" lasttarget
    overhead "Sails target saved! Cannons will aim here." 88
else
    overhead "No target selected - ShipSails unchanged" 38
endif

hotkey "Play Script: Bots\PoonerBot\base"
